---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import site from '../content/site/settings.json';

const { name, shortName, ein, address, phone, email } = site;
const fullAddress = `${address.street}, ${address.city}, ${address.state} ${address.zip}`;
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phone.replace(/\D/g, '')}`;
---

<PageLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  heroTitle="Terms of Use"
  heroSubtitle="Rules governing use of this website"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container--narrow legal-page">

      <p class="legal-updated">Last Updated: March 8, 2026</p>

      <p>Welcome to the website of {name} ("{shortName}," "we," "us," or "our"), a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization (EIN: {ein}). By accessing or using sunshineonaranneyday.com (the "Site"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Use. If you do not agree, please do not use the Site.</p>

      <!-- 1 -->
      <h2>1. Use of the Site</h2>
      <p>You may use the Site for lawful purposes only. You agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the Site in any way that violates applicable federal, state, or local law.</li>
        <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of the Site, its servers, or any connected systems.</li>
        <li>Use automated tools (bots, scrapers, etc.) to access or collect data from the Site without our written permission.</li>
        <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Site's operation or the servers and networks connected to it.</li>
        <li>Impersonate SOARD, its staff, or any other person or entity.</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- 2 -->
      <h2>2. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>All content on this Site — including text, photographs, videos, graphics, logos, and design — is the property of {name} or its content partners and is protected by U.S. copyright and trademark laws.</p>
      <p>You may not reproduce, distribute, modify, display, or create derivative works from any content on this Site without our prior written consent. Limited personal, non-commercial use (such as sharing a link to our Site) is permitted.</p>
      <p>The {shortName} name, "{name}" name, "Sunny and Ranney" name, logos, and "{site.tagline}" tagline are trademarks of {name}.</p>

      <!-- 3 -->
      <h2>3. Photos &amp; Stories of Children</h2>
      <p>The photos and stories of children featured on our Site are shared with the express written consent of their parents or legal guardians. These images and stories are provided solely to illustrate the impact of our work.</p>
      <p>You may <strong>not</strong> download, redistribute, or use photos or stories of children from this Site for any purpose without our explicit written permission.</p>

      <!-- 4 -->
      <h2>4. Donations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>All donations to SOARD are tax-deductible to the extent allowed by law.</li>
        <li>Donation receipts are issued via email for your tax records.</li>
        <li>Donations are generally non-refundable. If you believe a donation was made in error, please contact us within 30 days at <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>.</li>
        <li>SOARD reserves the right to allocate donated funds at its discretion to best fulfill its mission, unless a specific restriction is agreed upon in writing.</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- 5 -->
      <h2>5. Merchandise &amp; Shop</h2>
      <p>Purchases made through our shop are processed by Shopify and are subject to the following:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Pricing:</strong> All prices are listed in U.S. dollars and are subject to change without notice.</li>
        <li><strong>Shipping:</strong> We strive to ship orders promptly. Shipping times may vary.</li>
        <li><strong>Returns &amp; exchanges:</strong> Please contact us at <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a> within 14 days of receiving your order if you need to request a return or exchange. Items must be unused and in original condition.</li>
        <li><strong>Proceeds:</strong> 100% of net proceeds from merchandise sales support SOARD's mission.</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- 6 -->
      <h2>6. Room Makeover Applications</h2>
      <p>Submitting an application for a room makeover does not guarantee selection. SOARD reviews applications based on need, available resources, and other criteria at its sole discretion. All information submitted in applications will be handled in accordance with our <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

      <!-- 7 -->
      <h2>7. Third-Party Links &amp; Services</h2>
      <p>Our Site may link to third-party websites and services (e.g., Shopify, social media platforms, GuideStar, Charity Navigator). These links are provided for convenience only. We do not endorse, control, or assume responsibility for the content, products, or practices of any third-party site.</p>

      <!-- 8 -->
      <h2>8. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p>The Site and all content are provided <strong>"as is"</strong> and <strong>"as available"</strong> without warranties of any kind, either express or implied. We do not warrant that the Site will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of viruses or other harmful components.</p>

      <!-- 9 -->
      <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>To the fullest extent permitted by law, {name}, its board members, officers, employees, and volunteers shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of or inability to use the Site, even if we have been advised of the possibility of such damages.</p>

      <!-- 10 -->
      <h2>10. Indemnification</h2>
      <p>You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless {name} and its board members, officers, employees, and volunteers from any claims, damages, losses, or expenses (including reasonable attorneys' fees) arising from your use of the Site or violation of these Terms.</p>

      <!-- 11 -->
      <h2>11. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Georgia, without regard to conflict of law principles. Any disputes arising under these Terms shall be resolved in the state or federal courts located in Fulton County, Georgia.</p>

      <!-- 12 -->
      <h2>12. Changes to These Terms</h2>
      <p>We may update these Terms of Use from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last Updated" date. Your continued use of the Site after any changes constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.</p>

      <!-- 13 -->
      <h2>13. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have questions about these Terms of Use, please contact us:</p>
      <address class="legal-contact">
        <strong>{name}</strong><br>
        {fullAddress}<br>
        <a href={phoneHref}>{phone}</a><br>
        <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>
      </address>

    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding-block: var(--space-4xl);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--c-text);
  }

  .legal-updated {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--c-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-border);
  }

  .legal-page h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2vw, 1.35rem);
    margin-top: var(--space-3xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    color: var(--c-dark);
  }

  .legal-page h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--c-dark);
  }

  .legal-page p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .legal-page ul {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    padding-left: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .legal-page li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .legal-page a {
    color: var(--c-dark);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: color var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .legal-page a:hover {
    color: var(--c-yellow-hover);
  }

  .legal-contact {
    font-style: normal;
    background: var(--c-warm-gray);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    line-height: 2;
  }
</style>
